				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Is Violence a Guy Thing?
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1757633">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Alikat Astrae</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1757562#post1757562" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Sounds to me like Scotland ought to outlaw glass containers of any type for alcoholic beverages.  Beer and lager should only be available either in cans or Red Plastic Solo Cups.  And pub that uses glass mugs would be shut down permanently at the first Glassing.  And Glassing should be a crime with a penalty of no less than 10 years' imprisonment.<br />
 <br />
That ought to pretty up the population a bit.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div><div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Maledict</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1757568#post1757568" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Some stats and figures from my line of work and area.<br />
<br />
80 to 90% of all domestic violence is committed by men against women. When you look at repeat high risk cases, that figure rises to 95% or so.<br />
<br />
80%+ of robberies are committed by men. <br />
<br />
90% of knife crime committed by men. <br />
<br />
95% of gun crime committed by men. <br />
<br />
Murders - of the 8 homicides last year in my area, 100% committed by men. <br />
<br />
Even when you drill down to the 'lesser' violent crimes (Assault with injury etc.), you are still looking at an 75%+ rate of male suspects. <br />
<br />
Violence is predominantly a crime committed by men - and outside of DV, generally against men as well. Young men in particular make up the majority of victims and offenders for these crimes.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div><div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Ninetoes</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1757583#post1757583" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">In my experience, women and men are both capable of violence. The difference, if there is on, is the level at which men and women respond with violence. I've found that while men tend to get violent faster and at a lesser level of anger if you will, it generally takes longer and more anger for a woman to respond violently. This is based on my observations while bouncing, where men would swing at the slightest  provocation while women tended to not respond violently until much angrier. At least in my experience this meant no one wanted to break up a fight between two women because it was a much more violent and vicious engagement then two drunk mooks swinging at one another. <br />
<br />
Completely unscientific but that's what I saw as security.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Alikat<br />
folk have tried to do exactly that and I'm all for it! (banning the use of glass containers)<br />
but..you get this same basic problem/excuse coming up:<br />
those who genuinely enjoy a drink, especially of whisky and some other things, hate plastic glasses, doesn't taste as good out of them (seriously, it doesn't)<br />
So, many retailers/pubs were against it, but others supported it...and thus never got passed as a by-law<br />
<br />
best mate was a bouncer, some bastard bottled a fella and my pal got big slice up back of his head from bits flying everywhere.<br />
<br />
lot of the violence though occurs when folk leave, or when folk are sitting aorund drinking in parks etc (hence one reaosn they brought in anti-drinking-in-public laws)<br />
Buckfast bottles are notoriously thick and heavy, can easily cave your skull in never mind slash, indeed, it's so well known the necks of the bottles are that strong, they smash the bottle, leaving them with a neck of ragged glass they then plunge poor sods with. <br />
Cops and others been demanding for years that shit gets sold in plastic bottles, but hey, money talks....<br />
<br />
very good BBC video article on such <br />
<a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/8462042.stm" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/8462042.stm</a><br />
