				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Is Violence a Guy Thing?
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1757652">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							On a rounder note re violence, current thinking about reducing violence is to treat it as a public health issue, rather than a criminal justice issue. Some of the largest reductions in violence (Boston, Cincinatti, Strathclyde in Glasgow, Cardiff) have been achieved through using a public health approach to the issue that treats violence as a symptom of something else. <br />
<br />
The something else is often employment or housing, but can also be mental health issues. Depression in young men manifests as violence and rage in most cases, and over one third of young men have an untreated mental health issue when they enter the criminal justice system in the UK for example.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
