							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				80 to 90% of all domestic violence is committed by men against women. When you look at repeat high risk cases, that figure rises to 95% or so.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Can you provide a citation for this?  I have seen otherwise.  What I've seen is that domestic violence rates are remarkably similar between men and women, the difference is that male on female DV is more severe on average.<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				Where violence that requires medical attention and / or a fatality occurs men are absolutely the most significant offender.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Yes this is not surprising at all.
						</blockquote>
